title: The Middle of Things
creator: J.S. Fletcher
description: LibriVox recording of The Middle of Things, by J.S. Fletcher. Read by Kehinde. A habitual late night stroll down Markendale Square plunges Viner into the middle of things most mysterious and most perplexing. A murder, an imposter, secret papers, all combine to mystify even the police themselves. Is Hyde as innocent of the crime as he claims? What is the clue of the veiled woman and the diamond ring? Things are not what they seem to be and how can Viner prove the man’s innocence? (Summary by Kehinde) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (204MB)
subject: Librivox; audiobook; mystery
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
Here is the summary for this audio book from the librivox.org page as it doesn't seemed to have made it's way over her: "A habitual late night stroll down Markendale Square plunges Viner into the middle of things most mysterious and most perplexing. A murder, an imposter, secret papers, all combine to mystify even the police themselves. Is Hyde as innocent of the crime as he claims? What is the clue of the veiled woman and the diamond ring? Things are not what they seem to be and how can Viner prove the man’s innocence?"


A really great story and excellent reader. It didn't really lose my attention through the entire story with it's many twists and turns.
Thank you, flambeau, for bringing this to our attention; the summary is now in place at the top of the page.
This is very enjoyable.  If you like mysteries I would recommend you download and listen to this one.

The story opens with an older lady, Miss Pankridge, lecturing her nephew Viner on how murder and adventure lurk around every corner.  He scoffs, but she insists and provides several examples.  After she goes to sleep, he takes a walk...  into a murder victim.  Ah the foreshadowing!  :-) 

Now Viner and Miss Pankridge are not the sort to let this opportunity go unchecked, they join in the fun of solving this complicated murder mystery.  

It was well read, well written, and a fun story overall.  Enjoy!
A great listen, enjoyed this very much, holds your interest until the end, read very well.
and a fine mystery story. thanks librivox and Internet Archive volunteers and staff
